HEADWORD: Anastomosis
<hw>A*nas`to*mo"sis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Anastomoses</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ opening, fr. <?/ to furnish with a mouth or
opening, to open; <?/ + <?/ mouth: cf. F. <ets>anastomose</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat. & Bot.)</fld> <def>The inosculation of vessels, or
intercommunication between two or more vessels or nerves, as the cross
communication between arteries or veins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

